City Controller

   The City Controller serves as the City's chief financial officer. The
   Office of the City Controller certifies the availability of funds prior
   to City Council approval of City commitments, processes and monitors
   disbursements exceeding one billion dollars annually, invests the
   City's funds, conducts internal audits of the City's departments and
   federal grant programs, operates and maintains its financial management
   system, conducts the sale of public improvement and revenue bonds and
   produces a comprehensive annual report of City finances (CAFR).

